TO VALIDATE KTL CUSTOMERS (JAPANESE ACCOUNT)
.BLANK
.BLANK
1)we are to receive a phone call from international informing us they
have submitted a request to establish a new ktl customer.
the following statement should be under the comments section:
.blank
     set up a customer as a tymuse customer not receiving his
     own data but sending it to customer 15898 (tymktl). do not install
schema. validate on host 23 **and** 34, using 23 as the home system.
.blank
2)once we are aware of the request, examine and process it into a separate
commands file. run the file as soon as possible.
.blank
3)when the new user is established, submit a request in 1validate
to "add user" to  sys. 34. examine and process your request.
.blank
4)reenter 1validate and submit a request to "set tymuse". note:
do not set tymuse schema. examine and process your request.
.blank
5)WRITE THE TWO REQUEST NUMBERS YOU SUBMITTED ON THE FRONT OF THE
original request submitted by international.
.blank
EXAMPLE:
1VALIDATE - VERSION  50.27
